WEBVTT

00:04.750 --> 00:07.420
♪ Magic is real here ♪

00:07.500 --> 00:10.340
♪ Far away from home ♪

00:10.420 --> 00:12.130
♪ Anything can happen ♪

00:12.220 --> 00:15.260
♪ When witches make the rules ♪

00:15.340 --> 00:17.640
♪ Monsters are cool ♪

00:17.720 --> 00:20.810
♪ The moon is our friend ♪

00:20.890 --> 00:22.980
♪ I want to stay with you ♪

00:23.060 --> 00:27.440
♪ On Summer Camp Island ♪

00:27.520 --> 00:35.450
♪♪

00:35.530 --> 00:36.570
[ Sighs ]

00:36.660 --> 00:38.370
[ Keys jingling ]

00:38.450 --> 00:40.620
Jimjams, I'm home.

00:40.700 --> 00:43.120
Where does he get the nerve,
haunting me like that?

00:43.200 --> 00:45.670
Lingering?
You burp them into this world,

00:45.750 --> 00:47.920
and they take
and they take and they take.

00:48.000 --> 00:49.790
Jimjams: He could use
the tough love.

00:49.880 --> 00:51.630
He'll be a better ghost
for it.

00:51.710 --> 00:53.300
Susie?

00:53.380 --> 00:54.920
I'm just thinking...

00:55.010 --> 00:57.340
the way he would badger me
about my emotional intelligence.

00:57.430 --> 01:00.640
I think I might...
miss him.

01:00.720 --> 01:02.140
Hey!
Snap out of it!

01:02.220 --> 01:04.020
You know how bananas
you sound right now?

01:04.100 --> 01:07.440
[ Sighs ] You're right.
I need to sleep.

01:07.520 --> 01:10.940
Attention all hags...

01:11.020 --> 01:12.110
I had a weird day.

01:12.190 --> 01:14.150
I need a full and healthy
REM cycle.

01:14.240 --> 01:17.070
You all better stay
in your cabins and be good...

01:17.160 --> 01:18.660
or else.

01:18.740 --> 01:20.160
[ Farting ]

01:20.240 --> 01:23.620
[ Chuckling ] Hey, Jimjams,
where'd you put my pants?

01:23.700 --> 01:25.040
I think I feel a draft.

01:25.120 --> 01:26.960
Susie, I think
you left the, uh,

01:27.040 --> 01:28.420
mic on.
What?

01:28.500 --> 01:30.000
Oh, man.

01:30.080 --> 01:33.510
Is there going to be
a sky announcement every night?

01:33.590 --> 01:35.630
Okay, where were we?

01:35.720 --> 01:38.340
"Dear Mom and Dad,
sorry I haven't written yet.

01:38.430 --> 01:40.300
Finishing school is going great.

01:40.390 --> 01:42.180
I have a big group
of friends already.

01:42.260 --> 01:44.520
We've been together a lot...

01:44.600 --> 01:45.770
a lot.

01:45.850 --> 01:48.520
So I'm definitely ready
for a solo night.

01:48.600 --> 01:50.310
Not that being in a group
is bad,

01:50.400 --> 01:53.190
it's just I need
some time alone."

01:53.270 --> 01:54.530
Oh!

01:54.610 --> 01:56.070
"By the way, Mom,
they've got me back in a dress!

01:56.150 --> 01:57.450
Love, Betsy."

01:57.530 --> 01:58.700
Stop.

01:58.780 --> 02:00.490
Time to get out of this thing.

02:00.570 --> 02:03.030
Pants on!

02:03.120 --> 02:05.370
Oh!
Did you see that, Hippograph?

02:05.450 --> 02:06.750
It moved!

02:06.830 --> 02:08.410
I think I'm getting better.

02:08.500 --> 02:11.170
And now...Betsy time!

02:11.250 --> 02:12.420
[ Thud! ]

02:12.500 --> 02:13.670
Betsy!

02:13.750 --> 02:15.710
Alice?
What are you doing?

02:15.800 --> 02:17.170
Put on your galoshes.

02:17.260 --> 02:18.680
We're going yeti skipping.

02:18.760 --> 02:19.720
We?

02:19.800 --> 02:20.930
Yeah!
Everyone's here!

02:21.010 --> 02:22.260
What are you doing?
This is dumb!

02:22.350 --> 02:24.890
Aren't we supposed to stay
in our cabins?

02:24.970 --> 02:26.180
Rest our personalities?

02:26.270 --> 02:29.600
No! Come on,
this is your initiation!

02:29.690 --> 02:32.230
If you want to be a witch,
you got to be in a coven.

02:32.310 --> 02:34.570
You want to be a witch,
right?

02:34.650 --> 02:37.690
I do, but...

02:37.780 --> 02:39.360
Betsy.

02:39.450 --> 02:41.030
Great!
Let's go!
Aah!

02:42.450 --> 02:43.530
This is fun, right?!

02:43.620 --> 02:44.950
Shouldn't you be
looking ahead?

02:45.030 --> 02:47.620
Pfft, I can practically fly
with my eyes closed.

02:47.700 --> 02:48.960
Whoa!
Hey!

02:49.040 --> 02:50.870
♪ Dundundundundundundun ♪

02:50.960 --> 02:53.330
Come on, Betsy,
do it with me.

02:53.420 --> 02:56.250
Both:
♪ Dundundundundundundun ♪

02:56.340 --> 02:57.800
Oh, hey, we're here.

02:57.880 --> 02:59.670
[ Yetis walla'ing ]

02:59.760 --> 03:01.010
Come on, come on.

03:01.090 --> 03:03.430
Okay, Betsy,
for your initiation,

03:03.510 --> 03:05.220
you're going yeti skipping.

03:05.310 --> 03:07.270
Yeti skipping?
Yeah.

03:07.350 --> 03:11.100
You go over to a clump of yetis,
you say hi to four of them,

03:11.190 --> 03:13.940
and then [clicks tongue]
skip the fifth one.

03:14.020 --> 03:15.020
[ Laughter ]

03:15.110 --> 03:16.860
Doesn't the fifth one
feel bad?

03:16.940 --> 03:18.320
For, like, 20 seconds.

03:18.400 --> 03:19.690
He'll get over it.

03:19.780 --> 03:21.740
Don't worry.
It's harmless.

03:21.820 --> 03:22.990
They really don't mind.

03:23.070 --> 03:26.120
It's like a fly buzzing
in their ear.

03:26.200 --> 03:27.790
Okay.
I'll do it.

03:27.870 --> 03:29.540
[ Yetis walla'ing ]

03:33.210 --> 03:35.080
[ Clears throat ]

03:35.170 --> 03:38.210
Um...hello.

03:38.300 --> 03:39.800
Hi.

03:39.880 --> 03:41.380
Hello, you two.

03:41.470 --> 03:43.130
[ Yetis walla ]

03:43.220 --> 03:44.340
[ Inhales deeply ]

03:44.430 --> 03:48.350
♪♪

03:48.430 --> 03:49.470
Hi.

03:49.560 --> 03:51.980
Guys, I did it!

03:52.060 --> 03:53.900
There, I did it.
Happy?

03:53.980 --> 03:55.650
No.
You didn't do it.

03:55.730 --> 03:58.020
You definitely said hi
to that fifth yeti.

03:58.110 --> 04:00.490
I'm sorry.
I-I just couldn't ice him.

04:00.570 --> 04:02.400
It's fine.
You basically did it.

04:02.490 --> 04:04.030
We should just say
she's initiated

04:04.110 --> 04:05.530
and go have
a cute little tea party.

04:05.620 --> 04:09.540
Mm, we should probably
do another initiation task.

04:09.620 --> 04:11.750
Wah! Wah wah!

04:11.830 --> 04:13.250
What's he saying?

04:13.330 --> 04:17.170
Okay, my Yeti's
a little rusty, but...

04:17.250 --> 04:18.500
Enter on meadow.

04:18.590 --> 04:21.010
And they have
the baseness's.

04:21.090 --> 04:23.680
It is not to --
to say hello?

04:23.760 --> 04:26.050
We may hate
yeti skipping

04:26.140 --> 04:30.680
and only continued
because it was traditional.

04:30.770 --> 04:33.180
Betsy is a hero
for ending.

04:33.270 --> 04:35.270
[ Walla'ing ]

04:35.350 --> 04:36.560
What now?

04:36.650 --> 04:37.810
He's saying...

04:37.900 --> 04:41.530
that as we honor her,
come, stomp.

04:41.610 --> 04:43.610
Watch out for jubilee.

04:43.700 --> 04:45.240
[ Stomping ]

04:45.320 --> 04:47.410
Uh, guys...

04:47.490 --> 04:49.700
Woo-hoo.
Whoo!

04:49.780 --> 04:50.910
[ All gasp ]

04:50.990 --> 04:53.040
I just wanted everyone
to feel included!

04:53.120 --> 04:54.790
[ Walla'ing ]

04:54.870 --> 04:56.250
[ Branch cracks ]

04:56.330 --> 04:57.500
-Poof.
-Poof.

04:57.580 --> 04:59.500
-Poof.
-Poof! Poof!

04:59.590 --> 05:01.590
Let's hang out forever!

05:01.670 --> 05:03.760
Aah.

05:03.840 --> 05:04.920
Aah!

05:05.010 --> 05:06.470
Ohh!

05:06.550 --> 05:08.220
Aah!

05:08.300 --> 05:10.430
Whoa, oh!

05:10.510 --> 05:12.100
[ All sigh ]

05:12.180 --> 05:15.390
It is just so nice
to know how to poof.

05:15.480 --> 05:16.810
That's why it's one
of the first things

05:16.890 --> 05:18.230
they teach us around here.

05:18.310 --> 05:21.230
Which reminds me, Susie still
needs to teach --

05:21.320 --> 05:22.480
Betsy!!

05:22.570 --> 05:23.690
[ Gasps ]
Do you think she's...

05:23.780 --> 05:26.240
No.
I do not think "she's."

05:26.320 --> 05:28.570
And we're gonna find her
warm, living body.

05:28.660 --> 05:29.950
Right away.

05:30.030 --> 05:32.120
But we already pushed
our luck yeti skipping

05:32.200 --> 05:33.950
against Susie's wishes.

05:34.040 --> 05:35.370
Susie Shmoozy.

05:35.460 --> 05:37.000
She wouldn't wake up
if the island were being invaded

05:37.080 --> 05:38.250
by witch hunters.

05:38.330 --> 05:41.540
Come with me or I say
you're no good!

05:41.630 --> 05:42.590
[ Wind howling ]

05:42.670 --> 05:43.880
[ Shivering ]

05:43.960 --> 05:46.260
I'm sure this is all part
of the initiation.

05:46.340 --> 05:47.800
Nothing to worry about at all.

05:47.880 --> 05:51.550
Just don't scream and the coven
will pop out of the snow

05:51.640 --> 05:56.100
and say, "You did it, Betsy.
You are so brave."

05:56.180 --> 05:58.560
"Dear Mom and Dad,
I'm making friends.

05:58.640 --> 06:00.100
I'm part of the group.

06:00.190 --> 06:01.690
Everybody loves me."

06:01.770 --> 06:03.320
Pbht.

06:03.400 --> 06:06.860
I should be sipping chamomile
tea in my cozy little bed.

06:06.940 --> 06:08.450
I should've stayed in.

06:08.530 --> 06:11.030
[ Swamp voice screams ]
[ Gasps ]

06:11.120 --> 06:15.040
"Dear Mom and Dad, my situation
is improving all the time.

06:15.120 --> 06:16.450
We've transitioned from

06:16.540 --> 06:18.210
'definitely going to become
a hippopsicle'

06:18.290 --> 06:21.040
to 'definitely going to be eaten
by a family of alligators.'

06:21.130 --> 06:23.800
Now, that's what
I call progress."

06:23.880 --> 06:25.300
The screams are probably just...

06:25.380 --> 06:26.710
joyous screams.

06:26.800 --> 06:28.880
Do you know where
my friend lives?

06:28.970 --> 06:30.220
Aah!
Ah!

06:30.300 --> 06:32.550
I'm sorry, are those ants
playing tennis?

06:32.640 --> 06:33.810
What is tennis?

06:33.890 --> 06:34.930
"What is tennis?"

06:35.010 --> 06:36.930
Now, that's
a silly question.

06:37.020 --> 06:38.560
I have lots
of silly questions,

06:38.640 --> 06:40.980
like, do you know
where my friend lives,

06:41.060 --> 06:42.770
or are you a witch
by any chance?

06:42.860 --> 06:46.030
Oh, uh,
I suppose I'm a witch.

06:46.110 --> 06:47.820
Wow.
I suppose a witch.

06:47.900 --> 06:48.900
That's so cool.

06:48.990 --> 06:50.320
My friend
is a witch, too.

06:50.400 --> 06:52.320
I was just on my way
to see her.

06:52.410 --> 06:53.870
Hey, that's great.

06:53.950 --> 06:55.870
Do you know how to get back
to the witch school?

06:55.950 --> 06:57.620
Oh, um...

06:57.700 --> 06:58.830
Where's the witch school?

06:58.910 --> 07:01.040
No, I'm asking you.

07:01.120 --> 07:03.500
You tell me
and I'll tell you.

07:03.580 --> 07:04.500
I don't know.

07:04.590 --> 07:06.340
It's somewhere
on the island?

07:06.420 --> 07:09.340
Full of witches that I was
just getting to know

07:09.420 --> 07:12.340
before they abandoned me
in an avalanche?

07:12.430 --> 07:15.010
I truly have no idea
what you are talking about.

07:15.100 --> 07:16.180
But you know who might?

07:16.260 --> 07:17.890
Actually, you know what?

07:17.970 --> 07:19.350
I don't want to go back.

07:19.430 --> 07:21.520
Great, you can hang out
here with me,

07:21.600 --> 07:23.770
and I can tell you
a long, sad story

07:23.860 --> 07:25.980
about the demise
of a friendship

07:26.070 --> 07:28.280
between two witches.

07:28.360 --> 07:29.610
Mm.

07:29.690 --> 07:31.700
Honestly not feeling
super receptive to friendship

07:31.780 --> 07:34.070
as a topic right now.
Oh.

07:34.160 --> 07:37.290
But we can talk about
literally anything else.

07:37.370 --> 07:39.450
Will you kindly
list some topics?

07:39.540 --> 07:42.540
You know,
politics, literature,

07:42.620 --> 07:43.830
yesterday's weather,

07:43.920 --> 07:46.590
emotional repression,
universal entropy.

07:46.670 --> 07:48.050
Oh, or pants.

07:48.130 --> 07:49.050
I know pants.

07:49.130 --> 07:51.220
He knows pants.
I love pants.

07:51.300 --> 07:53.630
I don't own any, but I've
looked at them a bunch.

07:53.720 --> 07:55.720
Now, just where on earth
do you look at pants

07:55.800 --> 07:57.390
in this wretched
stink pit?

07:57.470 --> 07:58.560
Right over there.

07:58.640 --> 08:00.520
Swamp voice:<i> Boo Jeans.</i>

08:00.600 --> 08:01.890
Do you think
they're open?

08:01.980 --> 08:03.230
They're always open.

08:03.310 --> 08:04.600
Ghosts don't sleep.

08:04.690 --> 08:06.520
Shall we?

08:06.610 --> 08:08.570
Oh, yeah, it might not...

08:08.650 --> 08:10.610
[ Giggles ]
That's fine.

08:10.690 --> 08:12.950
I can just...

08:13.030 --> 08:14.410
[ Bell over door rings ]

08:14.490 --> 08:15.950
Both: Wow.

08:16.030 --> 08:17.910
It's glorious.

08:17.990 --> 08:19.240
Glorious indeed.

08:19.330 --> 08:21.540
Welcome to Boo Jeans
by Pendarvis.

08:21.620 --> 08:24.080
I'm Jacques Pendarvis,
and I have touched

08:24.170 --> 08:26.790
every pair of pants
you see before you.

08:26.880 --> 08:28.420
I touched them all.

08:28.500 --> 08:32.170
But can't you, like,
not touch things?

08:32.260 --> 08:35.380
Vaporous ghost appendages
and all that?

08:35.470 --> 08:38.930
Your tactless discourtesy aside,
you are correct.

08:39.010 --> 08:43.020
The rats make the pants,
physically of course.

08:43.100 --> 08:47.190
No, I touch the pants
with words.

08:47.270 --> 08:50.690
You see, I compose each pair
of pants a poem

08:50.780 --> 08:53.650
before it begins its life
on the shelf.

08:53.740 --> 08:55.280
[ Clearing throat ]

08:55.360 --> 08:58.200
A worn again summer's day.

08:58.280 --> 09:01.330
A grassy stain
an' children play.

09:01.410 --> 09:04.120
A morning dew on wetted bum.

09:04.210 --> 09:08.670
Two leggeth lane steps
like a drum.

09:08.750 --> 09:10.920
Now, go ahead and browse.

09:11.000 --> 09:16.380
♪♪

09:16.470 --> 09:17.800
[ Both laughing ]

09:17.890 --> 09:21.970
♪♪

09:22.060 --> 09:24.230
Legs only, please!

09:24.310 --> 09:25.890
Sorry,
Mr. Pendarvis, sir.

09:25.980 --> 09:28.520
We just really like pants
is all.

09:29.730 --> 09:32.280
[ Both laughing ]

09:32.360 --> 09:34.610
This is, by far,
the most fun I've had

09:34.690 --> 09:36.030
on this dumb
little island.

09:36.110 --> 09:38.660
I feel like
I finally fit in...

09:38.740 --> 09:41.330
to this pair of pants.

09:41.410 --> 09:43.040
What's your name
by the way?

09:43.120 --> 09:45.330
Oh.
I don't have one yet.

09:45.410 --> 09:46.500
No name?

09:46.580 --> 09:49.540
I'm gonna call you
Ghost...the Boy.

09:49.630 --> 09:51.130
How do you like that?

09:51.210 --> 09:53.670
Okay.
I like it when you name me.

09:53.750 --> 09:55.630
And I shall call you...

09:55.720 --> 09:57.840
Nope.
I already have a name.

09:57.930 --> 09:59.050
It's Betsy.

09:59.140 --> 10:00.890
It's been a pleasure
enjoying pants near you,

10:00.970 --> 10:02.140
Ghost the Boy.

10:02.220 --> 10:04.560
And it's been a pleasure
being near you, Betsy.

10:04.640 --> 10:06.060
[ Clears throat ]

10:06.140 --> 10:09.560
I'd like to apologize
for my little outburst earlier.

10:09.650 --> 10:12.110
I'm just very passionate
about maintaining

10:12.190 --> 10:14.110
the dignity of my pants.

10:14.190 --> 10:18.280
But now I see that I interrupted
a rather charming montage,

10:18.360 --> 10:20.030
and I'd like
to make it up to you.

10:20.110 --> 10:21.740
Can I offer you anything?

10:21.820 --> 10:22.870
Anything at all?

10:22.950 --> 10:24.200
What you got?

10:24.290 --> 10:27.040
Well, I'm thinking of taking
Boo Jeans public.

10:27.120 --> 10:28.330
Would you like to buy stock?

10:28.410 --> 10:31.170
Our toad trousers
are blowing up!

10:32.290 --> 10:35.710
Let me get you some cucumber
water while you decide.

10:35.800 --> 10:38.590
I'll take one pair of your
finest pants please.

10:38.670 --> 10:40.430
Actually,
make that two.

10:40.510 --> 10:42.680
You know I can't actually
wear those, right?

10:42.760 --> 10:45.430
Yeah,
they're both for me.

10:45.510 --> 10:47.730
All: Betsy!

10:47.810 --> 10:49.600
Ugh, she's nowhere.

10:49.690 --> 10:50.940
What are we gonna
tell Susie?

10:51.020 --> 10:53.020
We can tell her
the morbid truth.

10:53.110 --> 10:54.730
No way.
Betsy is alive.

10:54.820 --> 10:55.900
Let's just keep looking.

10:55.980 --> 10:59.070
Ugh.
This island is so huge.

10:59.150 --> 11:01.740
She could literally
be anywhere.

11:01.820 --> 11:03.660
Betsy!

11:03.740 --> 11:05.450
Betsy: What?!

11:06.120 --> 11:14.210
♪♪

11:14.290 --> 11:18.210
♪♪

11:18.300 --> 11:20.300
Legs only, please!
